Web Beacons / Gifs ezHealthTrack uses software technology called clear gifs (a.k.a. Web Beacons) to help us better manage content on our web site by informing us what content is effective. These technologies are tiny graphics with a unique identifier, similar in function to cookies, and are used to track the online movements of Web users. In contrast to cookies, which are stored on a user\'s computer hard drive, clear gifs are embedded invisibly on Web pages and are about the size of the period at the end of this sentence.
